case_circumstances: On February 2, 1982, at approximately 13:50 hours, a woman whose identity is not knows was found hanging from a utility pole in rural McLean County on Route 136 near Le Roy, IL.  Who this woman is and why she apparently committed suicide is not known.
case_head_hair: Hair is shoulder length, black, with very small amount of grey
case_eye_description: Eye color is hazel or brown
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
case_clothing_on_body: Blue jeans, maroon V-neck sweater, rust cowl neck sweator worn under the maroon sweater, brown mouton (processed sheepskin sheared and dyed) 3/4 length fur coat, black pantyhose, white bra size 36C, pair of beige knit gloves.
case_footwear: Brown two eyelet Earth shoes size approximately 8-9, one white sock on right foot, one grey sock on left foot
case_other_items_with_body:
Contents of pockets- one pack Pall Mall cigarettes, one pack Now cigarettes, grey Bic lighter, small amount of United States Currency, M&M Peanut Candy, Key chain with seven keys.

It should be noted one of the keys found is traced to a New York City locksmith.  The tax stamps on the cigarette packs have been traced to southwestern Illinois and southeastern Indiana.
